cbb4ef142dc4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\n",
 StyleBox["This is a problem.  The MC for the splitting is not correctly \
sampling the distribution.  The blue sheet (upper bound for the MC sampling \
routine) must be higher than the peaks in order for the MC to work....\n\nThe \
previous results probably allow the quark pairs to split farther apart than \
they should.  The area under the blue sheet is practically a constant up to a \
cutoff around 1 fm, which means the MC is sampling a nearly-uniform \
distribution in rT.\n\nThis probably also then misses the effect of the \
mass-dependent shift in the peak.",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]],
 "\n"
}], "Text",
